  "cert_name": "ISO 27001 Lead Implementer",
  "lang": "en",
  "questions": [
    {
      "num": 1,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.1, what is the primary objective of monitoring and measurement activities in an Information Security Management System?",
      "tag": "Monitoring and Measurement",
      "options": [
        "C. To replace internal audits as the sole verification method",
        "D. To ensure that management reviews occur quarterly without exception",
        "B. To eliminate all identified non-conformities before they occur",
        "A. To determine the conformity of processes and the ISMS with requirements and to identify areas for improvement"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.1 requires organizations to determine what needs monitoring/measuring, methods for monitoring, analysis/evaluation processes, and timelines. The purpose is assessing conformity and identifying improvement opportunities.",
      "justification_wrong": "Prevention of all issues is impossible; internal audits cannot be replaced; quarterly reviews are not mandated by 9.1. Monitoring enables detection and improvement, not elimination beforehand."
    },
    {
      "num": 2,
      "text": "In accordance with ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.2 regarding internal audits, which statement correctly describes the auditor's independence requirement?",
      "tag": "Internal Audit Requirements",
      "options": [
        "C. Internal auditors must report directly to operational managers of audited departments",
        "D. Independence is only required for audits of critical information security controls",
        "A. Auditors must be completely external consultants with no prior knowledge of the organization",
        "B. Auditors shall be impartial and unbiased, free from responsibility for the area being audited"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.2.1(b) specifies auditors must be impartial and unbiased, and as per 9.2.1(c), shall not audit areas for which they have responsibility, ensuring independence and objectivity.",
      "justification_wrong": "External consultants not mandatory; reporting to operational managers compromises independence; critical controls don't exempt other areas. ISO 27001 requires systematic, independent audit approach across the ISMS."
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.3, what must be addressed in the management review regarding the performance of the ISMS?",
      "tag": "Management Review",
      "options": [
        "D. Annual compliance with external regulatory audits, excluding internal assessment results",
        "A. Only the number of internal audits completed and their financial costs",
        "B. The adequacy, suitability, and effectiveness of the ISMS, including performance against objectives and changes in context",
        "C. Exclusively the incidents that resulted in financial losses exceeding defined thresholds"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.3.2 requires management review to evaluate adequacy and suitability of ISMS, its effectiveness, performance against objectives, changes in context/risks, and competence of personnel.",
      "justification_wrong": "Clause 9.3 mandates comprehensive evaluation beyond audit counts or financial metrics alone. Management review must address systemic effectiveness, not just incident thresholds or external audits in isolation."
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "text": "In ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.1, when an organization identifies a non-conformity, what is the required corrective action approach?",
      "tag": "Non-Conformity and Corrective Actions",
      "options": [
        "A. Immediately terminate the affected process until external consultants provide a solution",
        "B. Take action to correct the non-conformity and determine root causes, then take action to eliminate causes of non-conformities",
        "C. Document the non-conformity and defer action until the next scheduled management review meeting",
        "D. Correct only the non-conformities that directly impact customer satisfaction scores"
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.1 requires organizations to take action to correct non-conformities (reactive) and determine/eliminate root causes (preventive). This two-fold approach ensures systemic improvement and recurrence prevention.",
      "justification_wrong": "Immediate termination is disproportionate; deferral until review delays mitigation; selective correction based on satisfaction scores contradicts ISMS principles requiring systematic treatment of all non-conformities."
    },
    {
      "num": 5,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.3, what is the primary mechanism through which an organization ensures continual improvement of the ISMS?",
      "tag": "Continual Improvement",
      "options": [
        "D. Focusing improvement efforts exclusively on controls that have experienced one or more breaches",
        "A. Replacing the entire ISMS documentation annually regardless of performance metrics",
        "B. Using results from monitoring, measurement, analysis, management review, internal audits, and corrective actions to improve the ISMS",
        "C. Implementing only the most expensive security solutions available to guarantee effectiveness"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.3 mandates continual improvement through systematic use of monitoring results, measurement data, analysis findings, management review outputs, audit results, and corrective action effectiveness.",
      "justification_wrong": "Annual replacement without metrics-based justification is wasteful; cost-based selection ignores risk; breach-focused improvement neglects preventive enhancements. Continual improvement requires integrated feedback loops across all ISMS elements."
    },
    {
      "num": 6,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.1, what is the primary objective of monitoring and measurement activities in an ISMS?",
      "tag": "Monitoring and Measurement",
      "options": [
        "A. To determine conformity of processes and the ISMS to requirements and assess the effectiveness of information security controls",
        "D. To document all security incidents for regulatory compliance only",
        "C. To replace internal audits with continuous monitoring systems",
        "B. To exclusively identify non-conformities and assign corrective actions immediately"
      ],
      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 9.1 establishes that monitoring and measurement shall determine conformity and effectiveness of controls. This supports performance evaluation and continual improvement through objective evidence.",
      "justification_wrong": "Options B, C, D misrepresent the scope. Monitoring is complementary to audits, not exclusive; non-conformity handling is separate; documentation serves operational purposes beyond compliance."
    },
    {
      "num": 7,
      "text": "In accordance with ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.2, what must the organization ensure regarding internal audit frequency and scope?",
      "tag": "Internal Audit Requirements",
      "options": [
        "A. Internal audits must be conducted annually regardless of organizational complexity or risk profile",
        "D. Internal audits must be performed only on critical assets identified in the risk assessment",
        "C. Internal audits are optional if the organization has external certification audits scheduled",
        "B. The organization shall plan, establish, implement, and maintain an audit programme(s) considering the importance of processes and results of previous audits"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 9.2.1 requires organizations to establish audit programmes based on process importance and prior audit results. This risk-based approach ensures systematic coverage aligned with organizational context.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option A ignores risk-based tailoring; C contradicts mandatory requirement; D limits scope incorrectly. ISO 27001 requires comprehensive audits across all ISMS elements, not selective coverage."
    },
    {
      "num": 8,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.3, management review must include analysis of which of the following?",
      "tag": "Management Review",
      "options": [
        "B. The status of actions from previous management reviews, changes in external and internal issues, information security performance, and the adequacy of resources",
        "A. Only financial performance and budget allocation for security investments",
        "C. Exclusively the results of internal audits and non-conformity trends",
        "D. Strategic decisions on control implementation without performance metrics"
      ],
      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 9.3.2 requires management review to include status of previous actions, context changes, performance data, resource adequacy, and stakeholder feedback. This ensures holistic strategic evaluation.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option A ignores performance and resource analysis; C omits context and stakeholder perspectives; D lacks measurement-based approach. Management review must be comprehensive per clause 9.3."
    },
    {
      "num": 9,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.1, when the organization identifies a non-conformity in its ISMS, what action must be taken immediately?",
      "tag": "Non-conformity Management",
      "options": [
        "B. React to the non-conformity by taking actions to control it, deal with consequences, and evaluate the need for corrective action",
        "D. Report the non-conformity to external auditors before taking any internal remediation steps",
        "A. Immediately shut down all affected systems until the non-conformity is completely resolved",
        "C. Document the non-conformity and schedule its resolution in the next quarterly management review"
      ],
      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 10.1 requires immediate reaction to control the non-conformity, address consequences, and assess corrective action necessity. This proportionate response protects information security while enabling investigation.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option A is disproportionate; C delays critical response; D prioritizes external reporting over control measures. ISO 27001 emphasizes timely control and consequence management."
    },
    {
      "num": 10,
      "text": "In accordance with ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.3, what constitutes a key requirement for corrective actions addressing identified non-conformities?",
      "tag": "Corrective Actions and Improvement",
      "options": [
        "D. All corrective actions must be identical regardless of the nature or severity of the non-conformity",
        "C. Corrective actions are voluntary; organizations may choose alternative improvement initiatives instead",
        "B. The organization shall determine and implement corrective actions based on root cause analysis, evaluate their effectiveness, and update the ISMS documentation accordingly",
        "A. Corrective actions must be implemented without prior evaluation of root causes to expedite resolution"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 10.3.1 mandates root cause analysis before corrective action, implementation, effectiveness evaluation, and ISMS updates. This systematic approach ensures sustainable non-conformity elimination.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option A skips root cause analysis; C removes mandatory nature; D ignores proportionality. Effective corrective actions require investigation, tailored implementation, and verified effectiveness per ISO 27001."
    },
    {
      "num": 11,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.2, which statement best describes the requirement for internal audit planning and execution?",
      "tag": "Internal Audit Planning",
      "options": [
        "C. Internal audit frequency is determined solely by management discretion without documented criteria",
        "A. Internal audits must be conducted at least annually, with audit scope, frequency, and methodology defined based on risk assessment and previous audit results",
        "D. Internal audits must focus exclusively on compliance with external regulations, not internal controls",
        "B. Internal audits are mandatory quarterly events with fixed scope covering all controls without exception"
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 9.2.1 requires organizations to conduct internal audits at planned intervals, determining audit criteria, scope, and methodology based on importance and previous audit results. This ensures risk-based approach to audit planning.",
      "justification_wrong": "Options B, C, and D contradict 9.2.1 requirements: B ignores risk-based planning, C lacks documented criteria requirement, D excludes internal control evaluation essential for ISMS effectiveness."
    },
    {
      "num": 12,
      "text": "In accordance with ISO 27001:2022 clause 10.1, what is the primary objective of corrective actions when non-conformities are identified?",
      "tag": "Corrective Actions",
      "options": [
        "C. To document the non-conformity without necessarily investigating root causes",
        "A. To eliminate the cause of non-conformity and prevent recurrence, with effectiveness evaluated and documented",
        "B. To assign blame to responsible personnel and implement disciplinary measures immediately",
        "D. To temporarily suspend the non-conforming process until external auditors review it"
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 10.1 requires corrective actions to address non-conformities by eliminating causes and preventing recurrence. The organization must evaluate action effectiveness (10.1.3), ensuring systematic improvement aligned with continual improvement requirement.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option B focuses on blame rather than improvement; C omits root cause analysis requirement; D represents reactive rather than corrective approach, failing to address systemic issues as required by 10.1."
    },
    {
      "num": 13,
      "text": "According to ISO 27001:2022 clause 9.3, what must the organization ensure regarding management review?",
      "tag": "Management Review",
      "options": [
        "D. Management review must be conducted daily to ensure real-time control over all information security activities",
        "C. Management review focuses exclusively on financial performance metrics unrelated to ISMS",
